page.title: 07SUBURBAN WILDLIFE TWO
page.content:
The{kingfisher}isn't very common but is still there.Along the{canal}there are a lot of water voles and rats and just as common are fishermen. If you walk around the fields when it is dark you will probably see a bat.These bats keep flying around near lamposts to find moths or flying insects.Around our area there is still a lot of wildlife to be seen.But at this rate with some of our{wildlife} either being shot or killed for sport there will not be much left.So let's preserve our{wildlife}and keep it that way so that everyone can see the beautiful wildlife that is around our area.
Pages 1-7 by Cranham Primary School Worcester
